<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//NSN//DTD DITA Task//EN" "nsntask.dtd">
				<task id="task_qjn_wjc_jtb"><title>Configuring IRI buffering</title><shortdesc>Use <cmdname>liconf liParams</cmdname> command to configure the IRI        buffering.</shortdesc><prolog><author>PEIPEI SHANG</author></prolog><taskbody><prereq>            <p>You must login as liuser to use the <cmdname>liconf</cmdname> CLI.</p>            <p>It is advised for the operator to create a separate <cmdname>tcpProfile</cmdname> to                be used when the feature is enabled. The recommended values are: </p>            <ul><li>                    <p><parmname>KeepAliveIdleTimer</parmname>: 10 seconds.</p>                </li><li>                    <p><parmname>KeepAliveInterval</parmname>: 3 seconds.</p>                </li><li>                    <p><parmname>KeepAliveRetry</parmname>: 2 seconds.</p>                </li></ul>        </prereq><steps><step><cmd>Configure the IRI buffering type.</cmd><stepxmp><codeph>liconf liParams --parameterName allowedIriBufferType                        --parameterValue AMF</codeph></stepxmp></step><step><cmd>Configure the IRI buffering capacity.</cmd><stepxmp><codeph>liconf liParams --parameterName maxIriBufferSize --parameterValue                        1500</codeph></stepxmp></step><step><cmd>Setup the IRI buffering for a QA CMM configuration.</cmd><stepxmp><codeph>liconf liParams --parameterName allowedIriBufferType                        --parameterValue both</codeph></stepxmp></step><step><cmd>Setup the max buffering capacity for a QA CMM                    configuration.</cmd><stepxmp><codeph>liconf liParams --parameterName                        maxIriBufferSize --parameterValue 4000</codeph></stepxmp></step><step><cmd>Disable the IRI buffering functionality.</cmd><stepxmp><codeph>liconf liParams --parameterName                        allowedIriBufferType none</codeph></stepxmp></step></steps></taskbody></task>